# install package

#load library 
library(ggplot2)

# Practice dataset for take home midterm 
data("ChickWeight")
# preview of data 
head(ChickWeight)
##   weight Time Chick Diet
## 1     42    0     1    1
## 2     51    2     1    1
## 3     59    4     1    1
## 4     64    6     1    1
## 5     76    8     1    1
## 6     93   10     1    1
# layering using "geom" functions
ggplot(data = ChickWeight,aes(x=Time, y=weight, group=Chick, color=Diet)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point()

# Adding Scales 
ggplot(data = ChickWeight,aes(x=Time, y=weight, group=Chick, color=Diet)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  scale_x_continuous(name="Time(Days Post Birth)", limits=c(0, 20))+
  scale_y_continuous(name="Body weight (gm)", limits=c(0, 400)) 
## Warning: Removed 45 rows containing missing values (`geom_line()`).
## Warning: Removed 45 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

# adding minimalist theme 
ggplot(data = ChickWeight,aes(x=Time, y=weight, group=Chick, color=Diet)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  scale_x_continuous(name="Time(Days Post Birth)", limits=c(0, 20))+
  scale_y_continuous(name="Body weight (gm)", limits=c(0, 400)) +
  theme_minimal()
## Warning: Removed 45 rows containing missing values (`geom_line()`).
## Removed 45 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

# adding facets
ggplot(data = ChickWeight,aes(x=Time, y=weight, group=Chick, color=Diet)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_x_continuous(name="Time(Days Post Birth)", limits=c(0, 20))+
  scale_y_continuous(name="Body weight (gm)", limits=c(0, 400)) +
  facet_grid(cols = vars(Diet), labeller = label_both) 
## Warning: Removed 45 rows containing missing values (`geom_line()`).
